## OWASP Top 10 Security Risks

### A01: Broken Access Control

Improper restrictions allow unauthorized users to access resources.

### A02: Cryptographic Failures

Sensitive information is not adequately protected through encryption.

### A03: Injection

Untrusted data is interpreted as commands or queries by an interpreter.

### A04: Insecure Design

Security weaknesses caused by poor application design.

### A05: Security Misconfiguration

Incorrect security settings expose systems to threats.

### A06: Vulnerable and Outdated Components

Use of software with known security vulnerabilities.

### A07: Identification and Authentication Failures

Weak authentication mechanisms allow unauthorized access.

### A08: Software and Data Integrity Failures

Applications fail to verify the integrity of software and data.

### A09: Security Logging and Monitoring Failures

Insufficient monitoring prevents timely detection of attacks.

### A10: Server-Side Request Forgery (SSRF)

Attackers manipulate servers into making unintended requests.

